    "id": "hv0276",
    "cat": "number",
    "topic": "Real Numbers",
    "q": "Which of the following is an irrational number?",
    "o": [
      "$3.14$",
      "$\\frac{22}{7}$",
      "$\\sqrt{10}$",
      "$-0.\\overline{6}$"
    ],
    "a": 2,
    "e": "$\\sqrt{10}$ cannot be written as a simple fraction of two integers, so it is irrational. $3.14$ and $\\frac{22}{7}$ are rational approximations, and $-0.\\overline{6}$ is a recurring decimal which is rational.",
    "d": 1,
    "s": "Y10.1",
    "diag": "concept"
  },
  {
    "id": "hv0277",
    "cat": "number",
    "topic": "Real Numbers",
    "q": "Identify the irrational number from the list below.",
    "o": [
      "$\\sqrt{4}$",
      "$\\pi$",
      "$\\frac{1}{3}$",
      "$0.25$"
    ],
    "a": 1,
    "e": "$\\pi$ is a non-repeating, non-terminating decimal, so it is irrational. $\\sqrt{4} = 2$, $\\frac{1}{3} = 0.\\overline{3}$, and $0.25 = \\frac{1}{4}$ are all rational numbers.",
    "d": 1,
    "s": "Y10.1",
    "diag": "concept"
  },
  {
    "id": "hv0278",
    "cat": "number",
    "topic": "Real Numbers",
    "q": "Which of the following numbers is irrational?",
    "o": [
      "$\\frac{5}{9}$",
      "$-2.5$",
      "$1.\\overline{23}$",
      "$\\sqrt{3}$"
    ],
    "a": 3,
    "e": "$\\sqrt{3}$ is the square root of a non-perfect square, making it irrational. The other options are either fractions, terminating decimals, or recurring decimals, all of which are rational.",
